1. cs.IT (Information Theory) - The paper deals with the diversity-multiplexing tradeoff of a communication protocol, which is a fundamental concept in information theory. 
2. cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) - The paper discusses a relay channel, which is a common topic in networking and internet architecture. 
3. cs.SY (Systems and Control) - The paper analyzes the performance of a communication protocol, which can be viewed as a system, and proposes a dynamic operation of the relay, which can be viewed as a control strategy. 
4. cs.COM (Computational Complexity) - The paper solves a convex optimization problem, which is a computational problem. 
5. cs.MM (Multimedia) - The paper deals with a MIMO (Multiple-Input Multiple-Output) channel, which is commonly used in multimedia communication systems.
